snippet: Former rebel forces used tanks and heavy artillery in an attack on Surt, the birthplace of Libya’s deposed leader, Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi; at Sidi Hamed cemetery in Tripoli, anti-Qaddafi fighters say they have found evidence of a mass grave.
lead_paragraph: Former rebel forces used tanks and heavy artillery in an attack on Surt, the birthplace of Libya’s deposed leader, Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi; at Sidi Hamed cemetery in Tripoli, anti-Qaddafi fighters say they have found evidence of a mass grave.
